docs: Event emitted when a token transfer occurs.
events.label: Transfer

docs: Event emitted when a token approve occurs.
events.label: Approval

docs: Modifies the code which is used to execute calls to this contract address (`AccountId`).
We use this to upgrade the contract logic. We don't do any authorization here, any caller
can execute this method. In a production contract you would do some authorization here.
messages.label: set_code

docs: Returns the balance of the owner.
This represents the amount of unique tokens the owner has.
messages.label: PSP34::balance_of

docs: Returns the owner of the token if any.
messages.label: PSP34::owner_of

docs: Returns current NFT total supply.
messages.label: PSP34::total_supply

docs: Returns the collection `Id` of the NFT token.
This can represents the relationship between tokens/contracts/pallets.
messages.label: PSP34::collection_id

docs: Transfer approved or owned token from caller.
On success a `Transfer` event is emitted.
# Errors
Returns `TokenNotExists` error if `id` does not exist.
Returns `NotApproved` error if `from` doesn't have allowance for transferring.
Returns `SafeTransferCheckFailed` error if `to` doesn't accept transfer.
messages.label: PSP34::transfer

docs: Approves `operator` to withdraw the `id` token from the caller's account.
If `id` is `None` approves or disapproves the operator for all tokens of the caller.
On success a `Approval` event is emitted.
# Errors
Returns `SelfApprove` error if it is self approve.
Returns `NotApproved` error if caller is not owner of `id`.
messages.label: PSP34::approve

docs: Returns `true` if the operator is approved by the owner to withdraw `id` token.
If `id` is `None`, returns `true` if the operator is approved to withdraw all owner's tokens.
messages.label: PSP34::allowance

docs: Destroys token with id equal to `id` from `account`
Caller must be approved to transfer tokens from `account`
or to transfer token with `id`
messages.label: PSP34Burnable::burn

docs: Returns a token `Id` owned by `owner` at a given `index` of its token list.
Use along with `balance_of` to enumerate all of ``owner``'s tokens.
The start index is zero.
messages.label: PSP34Enumerable::owners_token_by_index

docs: Returns a token `Id` at a given `index` of all the tokens stored by the contract.
Use along with `total_supply` to enumerate all tokens.
The start index is zero.
messages.label: PSP34Enumerable::token_by_index

docs: Returns `true` if `account` has been granted `role`.
messages.label: AccessControl::has_role

docs: Revokes `role` from `account`.
On success a `RoleRevoked` event is emitted.
# Errors
Returns with `MissingRole` error if caller can't grant the `role` or if `account` doesn't have `role`.
messages.label: AccessControl::revoke_role

docs: Grants `role` to `account`.
On success a `RoleGranted` event is emitted.
# Errors
Returns with `MissingRole` error if caller can't grant the role.
Returns with `RoleRedundant` error `account` has `role`.
messages.label: AccessControl::grant_role

docs: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See `grant_role` and `revoke_role`.
messages.label: AccessControl::get_role_admin

docs: Revokes `role` from the calling account.
Roles are often managed via `grant_role` and `revoke_role`: this function's
purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges
if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced).
On success a `RoleRevoked` event is emitted.
# Errors
Returns with `InvalidCaller` error if caller is not `account`.
Returns with `MissingRole` error if `account` doesn't have `role`.
messages.label: AccessControl::renounce_role

docs: Returns the attribute of `id` for the given `key`.
If `id` is a collection id of the token, it returns attributes for collection.
messages.label: PSP34Metadata::get_attribute
